<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-20T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-20T11:00:00-05:00" n="718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/84: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-20T17:00:00+01:00">January 20, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 20—1:50 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>3. Department’s telegram 45, December 8, 6 p.m. Forwarding pouch tomorrow
                            Austrian Government’s acceptance Senate reservation and <pb facs="0974" n="860" xml:id="pg_860"/> supplemental article signed today. Urge
                            Senate’s consent to supplemental article be obtained earliest possible
                            date. Will press for immediate ratification by Austrian Parliament.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>